Reference-contexts: This paper describes our ongoing efforts on building such pattern-recognizing agents into a UNIX shell, in particular, through the addition of a personalized software agent | a "personal assistant" <ref> (Mitchell et al. 1994) </ref> | to the UNIX shell tcsh. Before displaying a user's command-line prompt, the agent extrapolates from the user's past interactions with the shell and makes a prediction concerning what the user's next command will be.
