Reference-contexts: The approach taken here is to learn such functions by passively watching the user interact with the shell, and from such observations learn to predict the next command. This "learning apprentice" approach <ref> (Mitchell, Mahadevan, & Steinberg 1985) </ref> gathers data by recording, after executing each command, the state of the user's session with the shell and what command was executed.
